| image1    = Panthera tigris tigris.jpg|thumb
| width1    =
| alt1      =
| caption1  =A [[Bengal tiger]].
| image2    = Arabari.jpg|thumb
| width2    =
| alt2      =
| caption2  =[[Sal tree]]s in the [[Arabari]] forest in West [[Midnapur]].
}}

As of 2009, recorded forest area in the state is {{convert|11879|sqkm|sqmi|abbr=on}} which is 13.38% of the state's geographical area,<ref name="fsiwbforest">{{cite web|url=http://www.fsi.nic.in/sfr_2009/westbengal.pdf|format=PDF|title=Forest and tree resources in states and union territories: West Bengal|work=India state of forest report 2009|publisher=Forest Survey of India, Ministry of Environment & Forests, Government of India|accessdate=4 March 2012|pages=163<U+2013>166}}</ref> compared to the national average of 21.02%.<ref name="fsiindiaforest">{{cite web|url=http://www.fsi.nic.in/sfr_2009/chapter2.pdf|format=PDF|title=Forest cover|work=India state of forest report 2009|publisher=Forest Survey of India, Ministry of Environment & Forests, Government of India|accessdate=4 March 2012|pages=14<U+2013>24}}</ref><ref name=hdrchap9>{{harvnb|West Bengal Human Development Report|2004|loc=Ch. 9: Environmental Issues|pp=180<U+2013>182}}</ref> Reserves, protected and unclassed forests constitute 59.4%, 31.8% and 8.9%, respectively, of the forest area.<ref name="fsiwbforest"/> Part of the world's largest [[mangrove]] forest, the [[Sundarban]]s, is located in southern West Bengal.<ref name=mangrove>{{cite news
 | first = Sadiq
 | last = Islam
 | title = World's largest mangrove forest under threat
 | url = http://archives.cnn.com/2001/fyi/student.bureau/06/29/sundarbans/index.html
 | publisher = CNN
 | date = 29 June 2001
 | accessdate =31 October 2006
 }}</ref>
{| class="toccolours"  style="margin:1em; float:right; width:25%;"
|+ '''State symbols of West Bengal'''
|-
| '''State animal'''
| [[Fishing cat]]<ref name="wiisymbols">{{cite web|url=http://www.wii.gov.in/nwdc/state_animals_tree_flowers.pdf|format=PDF|title=State animals, birds, trees and flowers |publisher=Wildlife Institute of India|archiveurl= http://web.archive.org/web/20090304232302/http://www.wii.gov.in/nwdc/state_animals_tree_flowers.pdf|archivedate= 4 March 2009|deadurl= yes|accessdate=5 March 2012}}</ref>  || [[File:Fishing Cat (Prionailurus viverrinus) 3.jpg|50px]]
